CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 30, 1961, pg. 3 reads: "Peace On Earth - "If we can get along together, why can't people?" is what Tag, a soulful canine, seems to be saying to the world as he shares his lowly "pad" with Kitt, a felicitous feline. The two have called a truce in traditional was between cats and dogs - or at least for the duration of the holiday season.  They are the pets of Mr. and Mrs. Charles Harris of 7603 [7604] Mulford St. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Tag (dog) and Kitt (Cat) curled together in Kraft Miracle Whip box, on floor of home of Charles "Teenie" Harris with landscape patterned tray and shelf with iron and roaster
